<i>due to the massive blackout that occurred</i>
<i>at the same time as the attacks.</i>

31
00:02:21.341 --> 00:02:24.310  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Again with the funeral faces.

32
00:02:33.253 --> 00:02:36.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What happened in there?!
Why did you let Sato get away?!

33
00:02:36.256 --> 00:02:37.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whoa, hold up, Mr. Tosaki!

34
00:02:37.824 --> 00:02:39.826  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How did things go so wrong
with you there?!

35
00:02:40.493 --> 00:02:42.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your IBM should have crushed Sato!

36
00:02:43.296 --> 00:02:44.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Am I wrong?!

37
00:02:44.797 --> 00:02:46.366  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Say something, damn it!

38
00:02:46.432 --> 00:02:48.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tosaki, try to calm down.

39
00:02:48.835 --> 00:02:52.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's cruel to pin everything
that happened on Nagai.

40
00:02:52.906 --> 00:02:54.507  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Suzumura's right.

41
00:02:54.807 --> 00:02:56.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This isn't just Nagai's fault.

42
00:02:56.743 --> 00:02:57.644  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nagai] No.

43
00:02:58.578 --> 00:02:59.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It is my fault.

44
00:03:02.749 --> 00:03:05.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not being able to stop Sato...

45
00:03:05.418 --> 00:03:07.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hirasawa and the others getting killed...

46
00:03:09.489 --> 00:03:10.823  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's all on me.

47
00:03:14.627 --> 00:03:15.628  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can I go now?

48
00:03:18.498 --> 00:03:19.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, Nagai!

49
00:03:20.667 --> 00:03:21.935  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man on tv] <i>That was live from the scene.</i>

50
00:03:22.669 --> 00:03:25.305  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>The police are also seeking</i>
<i>the whereabouts</i>

51
00:03:25.371 --> 00:03:28.808  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>of Yuu Tosaki and Izumi Shimomura</i>
<i>of the Ajin Control Commission.</i>

52
00:03:30.310 --> 00:03:31.344  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tosaki.

53
00:03:32.879 --> 00:03:34.314  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Of course.

54
00:03:35.548 --> 00:03:36.916  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tosaki, what are you gonna do?

55
00:03:36.983 --> 00:03:38.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Always the fool, aren't you?

56
00:03:39.252 --> 00:03:40.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

57
00:03:54.834 --> 00:03:56.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's nothing we can do.

58
00:03:57.804 --> 00:03:59.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's already over.

59
00:03:59.872 --> 00:04:01.241  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Everything.

60
00:04:08.014 --> 00:04:11.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Actually, I'm the biggest fool here.

61
00:04:12.552 --> 00:04:14.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Trying to team up with Ajin...

62
00:04:15.321 --> 00:04:16.756  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, here's what happens.

63
00:04:16.823 --> 00:04:21.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Forget losing my job,
now I'm a criminal, too.

64
00:04:23.630 --> 00:04:25.498  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughing]

65
00:04:40.046 --> 00:04:40.913  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Sato] <i>So?</i>

66
00:04:41.714 --> 00:04:44.651  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>How does it feel,</i>
<i>seeing people die because of you?</i>

67
00:04:45.451 --> 00:04:46.552  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasping]

68
00:04:46.653 --> 00:04:48.888  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nagai] Please... ghost... come on!

69
00:04:50.990 --> 00:04:53.293  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come on!

70
00:04:56.596 --> 00:04:57.797  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sobbing]

71
00:05:16.449 --> 00:05:17.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're sure of this?

72
00:05:18.618 --> 00:05:19.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] Yes, sir.

73
00:05:20.453 --> 00:05:22.021  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It was all taken by Sato.

74
00:05:23.756 --> 00:05:26.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Damn...
Tell the prime minister immediately.

75
00:05:33.900 --> 00:05:36.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Prime minister,
if word of this matter gets out,

76
00:05:37.370 --> 00:05:39.505  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
the entire nation will fall into a panic.

77
00:05:40.406 --> 00:05:43.042  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is the threat that great?

78
00:05:43.810 --> 00:05:45.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If they were to use everything
they've taken,

79
00:05:45.812 --> 00:05:49.015  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it'd be possible to kill everyone
in the country three times over.

80
00:05:50.550 --> 00:05:51.617  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groans]

81
00:05:51.818 --> 00:05:54.787  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Prime minister, you should keep in mind
the worst case scenario

82
00:05:54.854 --> 00:05:56.656  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and prepare a settlement offer.

83
00:06:00.526 --> 00:06:01.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know.

84
00:06:02.128 --> 00:06:05.832  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Have that taken care of
while we continue the search for Sato.

85
00:06:05.898 --> 00:06:07.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

86
00:06:09.402 --> 00:06:12.905  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>As you can see,</i>
<i>the countdown is over.</i>

87
00:06:13.606 --> 00:06:18.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>But we never got a response</i>
<i>from the government.</i>

88
00:06:19.645 --> 00:06:21.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>It's a terrible shame,</i>

89
00:06:21.981 --> 00:06:27.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>but as I've said before,</i>
<i>we won't stop for anything.</i>

90
00:06:28.621 --> 00:06:30.590  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Therefore,</i>

91
00:06:31.057 --> 00:06:32.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>within the next ten days,</i>

92
00:06:33.693 --> 00:06:35.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>we will begin the final wave.</i>

93
00:06:36.629 --> 00:06:38.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>And though you've made it this far,</i>

94
00:06:38.698 --> 00:06:42.101  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>for those of you who still pretend</i>
<i>to have nothing to do with this,</i>

95
00:06:43.536 --> 00:06:46.506  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>there's no escaping now.</i>

96
00:06:47.406 --> 00:06:49.041  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>That was the Ajin Sato's...</i>

97
00:06:49.108 --> 00:06:51.077  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How far are they going to go?

98
00:06:52.078 --> 00:06:53.479  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is insane.

99
00:06:55.448 --> 00:06:56.716  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

100
00:06:57.850 --> 00:06:58.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Three, two, one!

101
00:07:00.920 --> 00:07:02.822  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Careful with those.

102
00:07:03.422 --> 00:07:06.459  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We may have more than one life,
but those don't.

103
00:07:18.738 --> 00:07:21.140  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sato's just playing around!

104
00:07:21.974 --> 00:07:25.478  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He doesn't give a damn
about a future for Ajin!

105
00:07:26.879 --> 00:07:29.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man] Why are you staring
into space like that?

106
00:07:30.616 --> 00:07:32.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thinking about food or something?

107
00:07:34.020 --> 00:07:35.087  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

108
00:07:37.757 --> 00:07:39.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, Tanaka...

109
00:07:39.959 --> 00:07:40.827  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah?

110
00:07:41.594 --> 00:07:42.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do...?

111
00:07:44.730 --> 00:07:46.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you think Sato really has our...?

112
00:07:47.467 --> 00:07:49.902  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-The Ajin's best interests--?
-I said it before.

113
00:07:50.903 --> 00:07:53.005  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We just have to trust him.

114
00:07:56.476 --> 00:07:59.779  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And either way,
the next step is the last one.

115
00:08:00.480 --> 00:08:02.081  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right, Tanaka?

116
00:08:02.748 --> 00:08:03.616  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah.

117
00:08:04.150 --> 00:08:06.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This will be it.

118
00:08:08.187 --> 00:08:09.055  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The end.

119
00:08:11.491 --> 00:08:12.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I sure hope so.

120
00:08:16.896 --> 00:08:18.498  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[humming]

121
00:08:21.968 --> 00:08:23.069  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[knocking on door]
-Hmm?

122
00:08:25.805 --> 00:08:28.040  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I got those architectural plans
we talked about.

123
00:08:29.275 --> 00:08:31.711  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I should be able
to finish entering the data

124
00:08:31.777 --> 00:08:33.613  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
for the underground tunnels today.

125
00:08:33.679 --> 00:08:36.249  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sorry, I've dumped so much on you.

126
00:08:38.651 --> 00:08:39.819  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm.

127
00:08:42.188 --> 00:08:44.190  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mm. Very good.

128
00:08:46.158 --> 00:08:47.660  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And how about that other thing?

129
00:08:48.027 --> 00:08:49.662  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think I can wrap it up on time.

130
00:08:49.729 --> 00:08:51.597  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're amazing, Okuyama.

131
00:08:52.265 --> 00:08:54.734  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My word, this is shaping up
to be another fun time.

132
00:08:56.636 --> 00:08:58.638  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This next one is the last one, right?

133
00:08:58.704 --> 00:09:00.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Sato] Depends on what the enemy does.

134
00:09:01.607 --> 00:09:02.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why?

135
00:09:03.809 --> 00:09:05.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No reason, really.

136
00:09:07.013 --> 00:09:07.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I see.

137
00:09:09.582 --> 00:09:10.917  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You can relax, though.

138
00:09:11.250 --> 00:09:14.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I intend to seriously negotiate
with the government this time.

139
00:09:15.254 --> 00:09:19.258  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's why we took what we did
from Musashi Industries.

140
00:09:19.926 --> 00:09:23.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah. Gotcha. I see what you mean.

141
00:09:23.663 --> 00:09:26.732  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We can't keep playing war games forever.

142
00:09:27.099 --> 00:09:28.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's right.

143
00:09:31.003 --> 00:09:34.140  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll just be getting back to work, then.

144
00:09:42.248 --> 00:09:44.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[woman 1 over monitor]
<i>The investigation has raised suspicions</i>

145
00:09:44.717 --> 00:09:46.786  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>that Dr. Ogura was kidnapped</i>
<i>by the Ajin Sato.</i>

146
00:09:47.119 --> 00:09:50.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>It was then that the safe house</i>
<i>was attacked by Sato.</i>

147
00:09:51.157 --> 00:09:54.026  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>First you move to ensure safety,</i>
<i>then you get back in contact.</i>

148
00:09:54.660 --> 00:09:56.796  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>That's the short version</i>
<i>of how it usually goes.</i>

149
00:09:57.597 --> 00:10:02.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>This e-mail was the last we heard</i>
<i>from Douglas Almeida and Carly Myers.</i>

150
00:10:02.835 --> 00:10:05.037  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>They disappeared after that,</i>
<i>and their whereabouts are unknown.</i>

151
00:10:05.705 --> 00:10:07.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[woman 2] <i>During the debrief</i>
<i>of the safe house guards,</i>

152
00:10:08.040 --> 00:10:11.844  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>we learned that they were under attack</i>
<i>from a small squad which included Ajin.</i>

153
00:10:11.911 --> 00:10:16.749  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man 1] <i>We've also heard that afterward,</i>
<i>there was a car chase in the vicinity.</i>

154
00:10:17.016 --> 00:10:20.319  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Given the circumstances, we have
to believe they were eliminated by Sato.

155
00:10:20.987 --> 00:10:24.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[woman 1] <i>Which would mean</i>
<i>that Sato does indeed have Dr. Ogura.</i>

156
00:10:25.157 --> 00:10:27.226  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Will you ask Japan</i>
<i>for an investigation?</i>

157
00:10:27.293 --> 00:10:28.661  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A waste of time.

158
00:10:28.728 --> 00:10:31.097  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't think they can stand up to Sato.

159
00:10:31.364 --> 00:10:33.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
However, if we send another team over,

160
00:10:33.799 --> 00:10:36.802  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we risk them meeting the same fate
as Almeida and Myers.

161
00:10:37.069 --> 00:10:37.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[woman 1] <i>So...</i>

162
00:10:39.005 --> 00:10:42.775  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Even if we wait for Sato's next strike,
that should give us enough time.

163
00:10:42.842 --> 00:10:46.412  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Depending on the scale,
military intervention may be an option.

164
00:10:46.679 --> 00:10:47.346  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[woman 1] <i>I see.</i>

165
00:10:47.913 --> 00:10:52.251  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>That would give us a legal way</i>
<i>to secure Japan's Ajin.</i>

166
00:10:52.318 --> 00:10:53.386  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Exactly.

167
00:10:54.253 --> 00:10:56.355  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll report to the secretary myself.

168
00:11:03.329 --> 00:11:08.801  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
SAMUEL T. O'BRIEN
DISHONORABLE DISCHARGE

169
00:11:32.258 --> 00:11:33.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What the...?

170
00:11:55.481 --> 00:12:01.087  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A day this beautiful deserves
a full frontal assault without subtlety.

171
00:12:02.088 --> 00:12:04.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've got a great show coming up
for you, folks.

172
00:12:20.840 --> 00:12:24.743  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Emergency! Emergency!
Armed terrorists are inside the base!

173
00:12:24.810 --> 00:12:25.911  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They destroyed our ammo stores.

174
00:12:25.978 --> 00:12:28.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>All guard squadrons,</i>
<i>head to Point 4 immediately!</i>

175
00:12:28.347 --> 00:12:31.450  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>We've confirmed that the terrorists are</i>
<i>armed with rifles and rocket launchers.</i>

176
00:12:31.517 --> 00:12:35.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Other units are to acquire live ammunition</i>
<i>in the main building.</i>

177
00:12:35.221 --> 00:12:38.357  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>This is not a drill!</i>
<i>Repeat! This is not a drill!</i>

178
00:12:38.424 --> 00:12:41.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Why can't we use the tanks!?
-The ammo was in the depot!

179
00:13:06.285 --> 00:13:09.155  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What the hell is with these guys?
-They're just charging in!

180
00:13:10.890 --> 00:13:12.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just neutralize them!

181
00:13:13.225 --> 00:13:14.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tanaka] <i>You guys...</i>

182
00:13:15.461 --> 00:13:17.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>can't stop us.</i>

183
00:13:21.233 --> 00:13:22.535  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go! Go! Go!

184
00:13:22.835 --> 00:13:24.170  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[all shouting]

185
00:13:26.038 --> 00:13:27.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it! Kill them! Stop them!

186
00:13:40.052 --> 00:13:40.953  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What the--?!

187
00:13:48.594 --> 00:13:50.062  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man screams]

188
00:13:50.462 --> 00:13:53.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've now lost the ammunition depot
and the armory.

189
00:13:53.098 --> 00:13:54.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We have reports that they are Ajin.

190
00:13:54.934 --> 00:13:58.204  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What?! Damn it, where is
the Central Readiness Force?!

191
00:13:58.270 --> 00:14:01.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They're en route,
but still need more time to get here!

192
00:14:01.273 --> 00:14:02.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell them to hurry!

193
00:14:02.541 --> 00:14:05.477  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're looking at a draft
of a settlement for Sato

194
00:14:05.544 --> 00:14:08.047  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that has been drawn up
by the Ajin Control Commission.

195
00:14:08.447 --> 00:14:10.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Prime Minister,
we have an emergency.

196
00:14:10.549 --> 00:14:13.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A ground SDF garrison
is under attack by Sato.

197
00:14:13.986 --> 00:14:15.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?

198
00:14:17.423 --> 00:14:18.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is Tanaka.

199
00:14:18.624 --> 00:14:20.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This area is secure.

200
00:14:20.626 --> 00:14:24.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Roger that.
Carry on with what we talked about there.

201
00:14:25.164 --> 00:14:27.233  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll be done here soon, too.

202
00:14:27.299 --> 00:14:28.534  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

203
00:14:28.601 --> 00:14:30.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] <i>Mr. Sato, wait!</i>

204
00:14:30.269 --> 00:14:32.271  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We won't be done here anytime soon!

205
00:14:36.275 --> 00:14:37.910  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't let them gain any ground!

206
00:14:37.977 --> 00:14:40.045  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We just gotta hold on
until backup arrives!

207
00:14:44.550 --> 00:14:45.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it!

208
00:14:46.018 --> 00:14:47.119  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Stay on target.

209
00:14:47.186 --> 00:14:49.622  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They're nothing but terrorists!
Keep killing them!

210
00:14:54.360 --> 00:14:55.394  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groaning]

211
00:14:57.329 --> 00:14:58.197  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What the...?

212
00:15:11.343 --> 00:15:13.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Heh. Didn't take long at all, did it?

213
00:15:13.946 --> 00:15:15.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right...

214
00:15:15.547 --> 00:15:16.415  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, then,

215
00:15:17.182 --> 00:15:19.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
shall we take this place over?

216
00:15:20.019 --> 00:15:20.686  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, sir!

217
00:15:27.960 --> 00:15:31.664  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Phew. I mean, that was easier
than I thought it'd be.

218
00:15:32.298 --> 00:15:34.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The SDF is bound by the law.

219
00:15:34.466 --> 00:15:37.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's a limit on the weapons
they can deploy right away.

220
00:15:37.269 --> 00:15:40.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It looks like our plan to secure
the ammo depot and armory succeeded.

221
00:15:41.373 --> 00:15:42.408  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nakano] Nagai!

222
00:15:43.075 --> 00:15:44.243  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nagai!

223
00:15:45.644 --> 00:15:46.578  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nagai!

224
00:15:50.716 --> 00:15:51.717  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nagai] This is...

225
00:15:53.052 --> 00:15:54.553  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
video from Sato.

226
00:16:01.093 --> 00:16:01.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Listen up!

227
00:16:02.261 --> 00:16:04.063  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
To support
the Central Readiness Force,

228
00:16:04.129 --> 00:16:06.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we have to protect this place
with our lives!

229
00:16:06.265 --> 00:16:07.299  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[all] Yes, sir!

230
00:16:23.182 --> 00:16:24.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Freeze!

231
00:16:31.190 --> 00:16:33.459  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know you guys have
to work around red tape,

232
00:16:34.226 --> 00:16:37.062  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I feel like I'm playing
on Easy Mode here.

233
00:16:42.034 --> 00:16:45.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Mr. Prime Minister, it seems
they've seized the command building.

234
00:16:45.337 --> 00:16:47.072  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How on Earth...?

235
00:16:47.339 --> 00:16:49.008  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's the situation there?!

236
00:16:49.408 --> 00:16:52.311  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They've pinpointed the vital structures
and locked them down.

237
00:16:52.611 --> 00:16:55.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Continuing to fight like this
will only increase casualties.

238
00:16:56.115 --> 00:16:58.217  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We will withdraw
in order to regroup our forces.

239
00:16:58.283 --> 00:17:00.352  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're just going to let them win?!

240
00:17:00.419 --> 00:17:01.553  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We are not.

241
00:17:01.620 --> 00:17:04.089  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The CRF is already deploying
around the perimeter.

242
00:17:04.156 --> 00:17:06.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can't we launch a counter-attack?

243
00:17:06.358 --> 00:17:08.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They may have chemical weapons.

244
00:17:08.360 --> 00:17:10.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Please, let us handle this carefully.

245
00:17:24.510 --> 00:17:26.545  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Sato, setup is complete.

246
00:17:27.146 --> 00:17:29.681  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Sato] <i>You really have a way</i>
<i>with machines, Okuyama.</i>

247
00:17:30.215 --> 00:17:32.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This was nothing.
These are standard models.

248
00:17:35.487 --> 00:17:39.124  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They sure look impressive,
but will they actually work?

249
00:17:40.125 --> 00:17:42.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is the latest model,
with auto-fire capabilities.

250
00:17:44.363 --> 00:17:46.065  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Was that supposed to be Okuyama?

251
00:17:46.465 --> 00:17:48.233  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[all laughing]

252
00:17:54.773 --> 00:17:56.508  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sniper squad, in position.

253
00:17:57.109 --> 00:17:57.776  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] <i>Roger that.</i>

254
00:17:58.343 --> 00:18:00.079  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The terrorists have taken hostages.

255
00:18:00.345 --> 00:18:02.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We don't move until we have a read
on the situation inside.

256
00:18:02.714 --> 00:18:03.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, sir!

257
00:18:07.853 --> 00:18:11.256  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Sato, the missile setup is complete.

258
00:18:12.224 --> 00:18:13.425  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Excellent.

259
00:18:14.159 --> 00:18:16.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Time to get this show back on the road.

260
00:18:23.635 --> 00:18:25.637  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Let's cut right to the chase.</i>

261
00:18:26.371 --> 00:18:33.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>We have prepared 20 high lethality</i>
<i>gas-loaded missiles for launch.</i>

262
00:18:34.113 --> 00:18:37.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You should already know</i>
<i>how effective they are.</i>

263
00:18:37.583 --> 00:18:40.552  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>These murderous weapons were developed</i>

264
00:18:40.786 --> 00:18:43.589  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>in secrecy at Musashi Industries</i>
<i>under government orders.</i>

265
00:18:44.423 --> 00:18:46.725  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Tanaka was their guinea pig,</i>
<i>as you'll recall.</i>

266
00:18:48.494 --> 00:18:51.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Here are our demands.</i>

267
00:18:52.331 --> 00:18:56.835  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Before 12 p.m. one week from today,</i>
<i>you are to evacuate Japan.</i>

268
00:18:58.704 --> 00:19:02.674  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>We will be founding</i>
<i>an independent nation for Ajin.</i>

269
00:19:02.741 --> 00:19:04.543  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Evacuate Japan?

270
00:19:04.610 --> 00:19:06.378  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is absurd.

271
00:19:06.445 --> 00:19:10.549  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Of course, I recognize</i>
<i>that this demand is extreme.</i>

272
00:19:11.216 --> 00:19:13.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>But the government</i>
<i>has given no indication</i>

273
00:19:13.752 --> 00:19:16.588  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>that they intend</i>
<i>to grant Ajin civil rights.</i>

274
00:19:16.788 --> 00:19:18.490  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>So, I am left with no other choice.</i>

275
00:19:18.724 --> 00:19:20.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I must resort to using force.</i>

276
00:19:21.193 --> 00:19:22.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All right!

277
00:19:22.895 --> 00:19:28.300  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I'm going to use this lethal gas</i>
<i>to kill everyone living in this country.</i>

278
00:19:28.367 --> 00:19:29.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[cell phone ringing]

279
00:19:32.905 --> 00:19:33.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

280
00:19:34.306 --> 00:19:37.442  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I think we have more than enough reason
for military intervention.

281
00:19:38.544 --> 00:19:42.314  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No, we cannot let him fall into the hands
of the Japanese government.

282
00:19:43.248 --> 00:19:46.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>As I expect all of this country's citizens</i>
<i>are well aware,</i>

283
00:19:48.220 --> 00:19:51.190  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I am not playing around.</i>

284
00:19:52.291 --> 00:19:53.825  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
END TRANSMISSION

285
00:19:56.528 --> 00:19:57.462  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tosaki] Suzumura.

286
00:19:58.597 --> 00:20:00.332  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can you handle weapons procurement?

287
00:20:02.401 --> 00:20:03.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Weapons procurement.

288
00:20:05.204 --> 00:20:08.707  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-That's possible, but why...?
-You know why.

289
00:20:09.341 --> 00:20:10.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We have to stop Sato.

290
00:20:10.776 --> 00:20:11.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

291
00:20:12.277 --> 00:20:13.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you serious?

292
00:20:13.779 --> 00:20:16.949  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-But we no longer have any backing.
-[Tosaki] That doesn't matter.

293
00:20:17.883 --> 00:20:21.386  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sato's already killed so many.

294
00:20:22.454 --> 00:20:25.224  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He won't hesitate
to push the launch button.

295
00:20:26.658 --> 00:20:27.526  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have to...

296
00:20:32.297 --> 00:20:36.001  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, this isn't just my problem anymore.

297
00:20:36.668 --> 00:20:38.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Suzumura, take care of it.

298
00:20:39.471 --> 00:20:43.442  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I follow orders. And that's all.

299
00:20:44.376 --> 00:20:45.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's what Hirasawa would've said.

300
00:20:48.347 --> 00:20:49.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

301
00:20:50.249 --> 00:20:53.652  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm not sure what's going on,
but we're taking down Sato, yeah?

302
00:20:53.719 --> 00:20:55.454  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-That's right.
-All right!

303
00:20:55.921 --> 00:20:57.923  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Time to get some payback
for the old guys!

304
00:20:59.524 --> 00:21:00.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nagai.

305
00:21:00.959 --> 00:21:02.294  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I won't do it.

306
00:21:03.362 --> 00:21:04.363  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What did you say?

307
00:21:14.306 --> 00:21:16.408  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
TO BE CONTINUED

308
00:21:17.643 --> 00:21:20.612  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[chorus singing]
<i>I'm tired of this one already, so</i>

309
00:21:20.679 --> 00:21:23.882  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I'll trade it</i>

310
00:21:23.949 --> 00:21:29.288  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>For your ordinary one</i>

311
00:21:30.422 --> 00:21:36.662  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>A shiny holy card</i>

312
00:21:36.728 --> 00:21:42.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>For a grainy paper card</i>

313
00:21:43.001 --> 00:21:47.406  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You can see them all</i>

314
00:21:49.541 --> 00:21:53.879  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>When you come to my house</i>

315
00:21:53.945 --> 00:21:59.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>So</i>
<i>Two of us in the corner of the schoolyard</i>

316
00:22:00.052 --> 00:22:02.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>While the wind blows</i>

317
00:22:02.421 --> 00:22:06.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I might be able to say it now</i>

318
00:22:08.727 --> 00:22:14.933  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Words I've never said to anyone</i>

319
00:22:15.000 --> 00:22:21.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>"Won't you come and play, I'll be nice"</i>

320
00:22:21.506 --> 00:22:27.412  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>"I'll give you anything, see"</i>

321
00:22:27.879 --> 00:22:30.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>"Be my friend</i>

322
00:22:30.716 --> 00:22:37.556  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Always"</i>

323
